(46, 1, '2018-10-10 06:37:09', '2018-10-10 06:37:09', 'The era of print media is almost over as enterprises are moving towards a more convenient and cheaper mode of marketing – Digital. It has been seen that the data consumption by the Indian population has multiplied manifolds in India since late 2016. There has been a tariff war going on between various telecom service providers. In the costly war, many companies have either gone out of business or merged with a more powerful one. The increased rate of data consumption has been the reason behind the demise of the print media. People are literally addicted to their smartphones and most of the information regarding anything and everything comes from the smartphones itself. This is the major reason that the enterprises have taken to the digital marketing platforms as it has a wider and faster reach, cheaper than the print media and easy to mark the target customers. Digital marketing is done via internet now a days called mobile digital marketing because most of the digital marketing scene.', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '46', '', '', '2018-10-10 06:37:09', '2018-10-10 06:37:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/techreview/?p=46', 4, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
