(125, 1, '2018-10-12 07:19:41', '2018-10-12 07:19:41', 'Artificial intelligence or AI is demonstrated by machines, in contrast to the natural intelligence displayed by humans and other animals. In computer science, AI research is defined as the study of “intelligent agents”: any device that perceives its environment and takes actions that maximize its chance of successfully achieving its goals. Colloquially, the term “artificial intelligence” is applied when a machine mimics “cognitive” functions that humans associate with other human minds, such as “learning” and “problem solving AI has a very wide scope in today’s technology and is quickly seeping into our daily lives. Smartphones and Laptops are coming equipped with AI enabled chipsets and camera modules. Most of the major technology giants have developed their own AI voice assistants, which help the users in getting their things done with just a voice command. These technological advancements are helping the users to get a more customized experience.', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '125', '', '', '2018-10-12 07:43:55', '2018-10-12 07:43:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/techreview/?p=125', 5, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(126, 1, '2018-10-12 07:29:12', '2018-10-12 07:29:12', 'AI is the buzzword for the technology business world now-a-days. Companies are more and more opting for digitalization and so are governments and law enforcement agencies. This is also the case with Dubai police. Dubai police is considered to be one the most advanced police departments in the world at least in terms of the money they receive, vehicles they have and technology they are provided with. However, they are lacking in one aspect now and that is predictive policing.\r\n\r\nPredictive policing is assessing the chances of a crime even before it happens and reducing the chances of the crime happening significantly. To perform such activities the need arises for technologies such as the all new Artificial Intelligence. This technology helps a machine detect the faces of numerous persons and run it through a database of people with prior police records.\r\n\r\nAccording to Business Line, Staqu’s innovation has led to the creation of various systems. Its Smart Glass technology enables police to get real-time information on anti-social elements and empowers them to analyse a crowd and segregate individuals based on their behaviour patterns, resulting in more precise actions.\r\n\r\nDubai Police has signed MoU with Staqu Technologies from India for AI based solutions on predictive policing. This is a good sign not only for Staqu but also for the Indian technology companies as a whole because it will build confidence among other entities across the globe for Indian technology companies. Funds will also come in from foreign entities and hence help them in growing manifolds.', 'Dubai Police ties up with Indian startup for AI-based solution on ‘predictive policing\'', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dubai-police-ties-up-with-indian-startup-for-ai-based-solution-on-predictive-policing', '', '', '2018-10-12 07:29:12', '2018-10-12 07:29:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/techreview/?p=126', 0, 'post', '', 0),
