(129, 1, '2018-10-12 07:31:02', '2018-10-12 07:31:02', 'Analysis: Smart TVs have been taking over the market in recent times. Electronic giants such as Samsung and LG have been fierce rivals from South Korea for very long. India being a very attractive market for new technologies, LG launched it voice control supported AI based TVs here. The new generation of TV buyers are not just looking for premium picture quality but also want their TVs to be smart just like their smartphones. TVs today can connect with the internet and surf online content. There is no need to open your laptop to watch any online TV series, smart TVs can do the work for you.\r\n\r\nIn old times the common scenario in many household was that there would be a quarrel among the family members for the TV remote. People would want the remote to change the channels. Then came the Xiaomi smartphones which allowed to control the TV with the phone itself. However, technological advancements now allow a person control the TV with his/her own voice.\r\n\r\nLG’s voice controlled TVs are priced at INR 32,000 which is quite affordable for the average household who are looking for smart TVs. Though the price is affordable, other competitors will belooking for opportunities to compete that very soon. Chines electronic giant Xiaomi and Indian Micromax are known for their TVs too. These companies and Samsung also launched TVs in India and they have the capacity to launch AI based voice controlled TVs in India at very competitive prices. This will benefit the Indian consumers as heavy competition results in lower prices and better quality.', 'LG Launches New AI-Based TVs With Voice Control Support in India, Price Starts at Rs. 32,500', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lg-launches-new-ai-based-tvs-with-voice-control-support-in-india-price-starts-at-rs-32500', '', '', '2018-10-12 07:31:02', '2018-10-12 07:31:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/techreview/?p=129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
